<h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Patch 36.1 (October 7, 2014)</h4><ul><li><b>Nightmare (Q)</b></li><ul><li> The power ratio of the allied proc damage portion of this ability has been reduced to 0.6, down from 0.7.</li></ul><li><b>Dreamwrap (W)</b></li><ul><li> The movement speed granted by this ability has been reduced to 20/22.5/25/27.5/30%, down from 30/30/30/30/30%.</li><li> The duration of a single activation of this ability has been reduced to 3 seconds, down from 4 seconds.</li><li> The power ratio of this ability has been reduced to 0.35 per stack, down from 0.4 per stack. </li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Patch 36 (September 30, 2014)</h4><ul><li><b>Reverie (R)</b></li><ul><li> Fixed a bug where reactivating this ability within a short window would occasionally fly Dibs to the center of the map.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 34 (August 19th, 2014)</h4><ul><li><b>Dreamwrap (W)</b></li><ul><li>The cooldown of this ability has been increased to 14/13/12/11/10, up from 12/11/10/9/8.</li></ul><li><b>Reverie (R)</b></li><ul><li>The cooldown of this ability has been increased to 140/130/120, up from 140/120/100.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 29 (May 5th, 2014)</h4><ul><li><b>Dreamwrap (W)</b></li><ul><li>The cooldown of this ability has been reduced to 12/11/10/9/8 seconds, down from 12 at all ranks.</li><li>The percentage movement speed increase granted by this ability has been increased to 30%, up from 25%.</li><li>The shield strength of this ability has been increased to 35/50/65/80/95 per cast, up from 25/40/55/70/85.</li></ul><li><B>Ripple (E)</B></li><ul><li>The cooldown of this ability has been reduced to 13/12/11/10/9, down from 15/14/13/12/11.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 27 (March 17, 2014)</h4><ul><li>Dreamwrap (W)</li><ul><li>The movement speed granted by this ability has been increased to 25% at all ranks, up from 10/12/14/16/18%.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 26 (Feb 24, 2014)</h4><ul><li>Nightmare (Q)</li><ul><li>The range of this ability has been increased by 2%.</li><li>The cooldown of this ability has been increased to 6/5.5/5/4.5/4, up from 4 at all ranks.</li><li>The Power ratio of this ability has been reduced to 0.5, down from 0.8.</li><li>The Power ratio of the ally Shaper damage component on this ability has been reduced to 0.7, down from 0.9.</li></ul><li>Dreamwrap (W)</li><ul><li>The range of this ability has been increased by 1%.</li></ul><li>Ripple (E)</li><ul><li>The range of this ability has been increased by 2%.</li><li>The Power ratio of this ability has been reduced to 0.6, down from 0.8.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 13 (October 13, 2013)</h4><ul><li><B>Nightmare (Q)</B></li><ul><li>The secondary damage that is inflicted when an allied Shaper attacks a target affected by this ability will now correctly credit the attacker with the Shaper kill or creep kill if the affected target dies.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 10 (August 23, 2013)</h4><ul><li><B>Nightmare (Q)</B></li><ul><li>The base damage of this ability has been reduced to 60/105/150/195/240, down from 70/120/170/220/270.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 7 (August 02, 2013)</h4><ul><li><B>Nightmare (Q)</B></li><ul><li>The base damage this ability dealt to enemies who take damage from an ally Shaper while affected by Nightmare has been increased to 60/85/110/135/160, up from 40/55/70/85/100. This secondary damage component has also had it's power ratio increased to 0.9, up from 0.6. The secondary damage component now only stacks once per target instead of up to 3 times.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 5 (July 18, 2013)</h4><ul><li><B>Nightmare (Q)</B></li><ul><li>The damage inflicted by an allied Shaper when damaging a target affected by Nightmare has been increased to 40/55/70/85/100, up from 20/30/40/50/60.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 1 (June 06, 2013)</h4><ul><li><B>Reverie (R)</B><ul><li>This ability is now smartcast by default for both its primary and secondary activations.</li></ul></li></ul>